## Testing Requirements

### Component Testing Standards

```typescript
// ✅ REQUIRED - Comprehensive component tests
describe("UserCard", () => {
  const mockUser: User = {
    id: "1",
    name: "John Doe",
    email: "john@example.com",
    role: "user",
    status: "active",
  };
  
  it("renders user information correctly", () => {
    render(<UserCard user={mockUser} />);
    
    expect(screen.getByText("John Doe")).toBeInTheDocument();
    expect(screen.getByText("john@example.com")).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
  
  it("calls onEdit when edit button is clicked", async () => {
    const onEdit = vi.fn();
    render(<UserCard user={mockUser} onEdit={onEdit} />);
    
    await userEvent.click(screen.getByLabelText("Edit John Doe"));
    
    expect(onEdit).toHaveBeenCalledWith(mockUser);
  });
  
  it("is accessible", async () => {
    const { container } = render(<UserCard user={mockUser} />);
    
    const results = await axe(container);
    expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
  });
});
```

## Code Quality Gates

### Pre-commit Requirements

All code must pass these checks before commit:

1. **TypeScript**: `pnpm type-check` - No type errors
2. **Linting**: `pnpm lint` - ESLint rules pass
3. **Testing**: `pnpm test` - All tests pass
4. **Formatting**: `pnpm prettier:check` - Code is formatted
5. **Architecture**: FSD boundaries respected
6. **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
7. **Internationalization**: All text uses Lingui macros
8. **Performance**: Proper memoization applied

